To some, this is very stupid, but this is what i could think of for now, I'll improve it later... hopefully🙏...<br> ANYWAYS, basically, this blog is powered by a simple JSON file that contains all the blog posts as objects with these attributes: title, date, body, and tags.<br>The post object structure looks like this:<br><pre><code class='language-json'>[
    {
        "title": "My First Blog Post",
        "date": "2026/03/09",
        "body": "This is a test to check if the blog page is working correctly.",
        "tags": ["Software", "Blog News"]
    }
]</code></pre> The JavaScript code fetches this JSON file and renders the blog posts on the page, aaaand that's basically it... I feel embarrased about this approach from how bad it is, it's really ineffiecient.<br>I bet you were expecting some databse with an API system going on, nope, just some JSON and JS magic.
